                                          comment: "<p>Granuloma formation is not classically seen in cirrhosis, which can be micro- or macronodular in type.</p>  <p>In the micronodular form, the nodules are less than 3 mm across with uniform liver involvement - seen in alcohol or biliary disease.</p>  <p>In the macronodular form, there are larger nodules, classically seen in chronic viral hepatitis.</p>  <p><strong>Further reading</strong>:<br />  <a href=\"http://www.onexamination.com/goto.aspx?url=http://www.meddean.luc.edu/lumen/MedEd/orfpath/cirhosis.htm\"  target=\"_blank\">Liver cirrhosis</a> Loyola University Chicago Stritch School of Medicine</p>  <p><a href=\"http://www.onexamination.com/goto.aspx?url=http://radiology.uchc.edu/eAtlas/GI/578.htm\" target=\"_blank\">Micronodular cirrhosis</a> eAtlas of Pathology</p>",
